Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object detection and instance segmentation using deep neural networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end trainable deep neural network architecture. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated object detection and segmentation. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the proposed architecture consists of convolutional and recurrent layers. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with detecting cars in the KITTI benchmark dataset, which has applications in robotics.
